<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 23 at 4:26PM MDT  by NWS Billings</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Wheatland County through 515 PM MDT...
At 425 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Harlowton, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Harlowton.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
